Description: NIKOS — Static Analyzer for C/C++ (LLVM 20)
 NIKOS (New Inference Kernel for Open Static Analyzers) is a production-ready
 static analyzer for C/C++ based on Abstract Interpretation. It is a modernized
 fork of NASA's IKOS, upgraded from LLVM 14 to LLVM 20.
 .
 NIKOS detects buffer overflows, null pointer dereferences, division by zero,
 use of uninitialized variables, double-frees, and 10 other defect categories
 with 64 regression tests passing.
 .
 Optional APRON support (13 relational abstract domains) can be enabled by
 building from source with -DAPRON_ROOT=/path/to/apron.
